A toothpaste factory had a problem: Due to the way the production line was set up, sometimes empty boxes were shipped without the tube inside.

CEO hired experts for $8 million, and they analyzed, designed and implemented solution: when scales showed less than a normal weight, a bell rung and line stopped. The result was &mdash; no empty boxes shipped. So CEO thought this is impossible and he went to the factory only to find &hellip;

Question: Name something which costs $20 which actually solved the problem?

One night of the year 2000 Sacramento resident John Casey was watching movie &laquo;Fly&raquo; in which genes of a fly and a man are mixed. Then John Casey thought of two gadgets he was always carrying in his pocket and &hellip;

Most people actually think that person with initials S.J. is an inventor of something that John Casey invented that night.

Question: What exactly, according to many historians, did John Casey invent, which some of you have right now in your pockets or purses?
